<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2012/09/20/spring-shell-1-0-0-rc1-released">Spring Shell 1.0.0.RC1 Released </a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="null?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Costin Leau</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2012-09-20 17:26:00.0">September 20, 2012</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1109" href="/blog/2012/09/20/spring-shell-1-0-0-rc1-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Dear Spring Community,</p>
<p>I am pleased to announce the first release candidate for Spring Shell project! Spring Shell is an interactive shell that can be easily extended with commands using a Spring based programming model, extracted from the Spring Roo project.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Shell&amp;version=1.0.0.RC1">Downloads</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-shell/docs/1.0.0.RC1/api/">JavaDocs</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-shell/docs/1.0.0.RC1/reference/html">Reference Documentation</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-shell/docs/1.0.0.RC1/changelog.txt">Changelog</a></p>
<p>This release contains various fixes related to JLine/Jansi. See the <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-shell/docs/1.0.0.RC1/changelog.txt">changelog</a> for detailed info. </p>
<p>We look forward to your feedback on the <a href="http://forum.springsource.org/forum.php">forum</a> or in the <a href="https://jira.springsource.org/browse/SHL">issue tracker</a>.</p>
</div>
</section>
